---
import ContentPageLayout from '../../layouts/ContentPageLayout.astro';
import { Server, BarChart3, Inbox, Bot, Briefcase, ShieldCheck, Mail, MapPin, Phone, User, Scale, Globe, Clock } from 'lucide-astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<ContentPageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - eFlury Consulting"
  description="Privacy policy of eflury.com under the Swiss revFADP: what data we process, which services are involved (Hostinger, HubSpot, Google Analytics, DeepSeek, Cloudflare), how long we keep it and what rights you have."
  lang={lang}
  heroTitle="Privacy Policy"
  heroSubtitle="What data we process, with whom, for how long — fully disclosed"
  lastUpdated="July 23, 2026"
  keywords="privacy policy, revFADP, FADP, data protection, DeepSeek, HubSpot, Google Analytics, eFlury Consulting"
>
  <p>This policy describes how we process personal data when you visit eflury.com or get in touch — under the revised Swiss Data Protection Act (revFADP) and, where applicable, the GDPR. We name every service we use, including the inconvenient details.</p>

  <h2>1. Controller</h2>
  <div class="dp-controller">
    <dl class="dpc-grid">
      <div class="dpc-row">
        <dt><User size={16} /> Controller</dt>
        <dd>Emanuel Aaron Flury<br />eFlury Consulting (sole proprietorship)</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="dpc-row">
        <dt><MapPin size={16} /> Address</dt>
        <dd>Keltenweg 4, 2540 Grenchen, Switzerland</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="dpc-row">
        <dt><Mail size={16} /> Email</dt>
        <dd><a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a></dd>
      </div>
      <div class="dpc-row">
        <dt><Phone size={16} /> Phone</dt>
        <dd><a href="tel:+41799107787">+41 79 910 77 87</a></dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2>2. What We Process — Service by Service</h2>
  <p>Instead of abstract categories: here is every data-processing activity on this website, listed individually.</p>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><Server size={18} /> <h3>Website &amp; server logs</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Delivering the website, stability, abuse prevention</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>IP address, browser type, pages visited, timestamp (technical log data)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>Hostinger (hosting, EU)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>Log data is rotated and deleted automatically by the host</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><BarChart3 size={18} /> <h3>Web statistics (Google Analytics 4)</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Understanding which content is used, to improve the website</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>Pseudonymized usage data (pages visited, time on page, device, approximate origin); GA4 does not store full IP addresses</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>Google (USA; certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>Per Google Analytics settings, at most 14 months</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><Inbox size={18} /> <h3>Forms &amp; CRM (HubSpot)</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Answering contact requests, sending the newsletter (double opt-in, unsubscribe any time), following up on download requests, managing prospects, documenting offer acceptances (contract formation)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>Name, email, phone (optional), message or request context; for offer acceptances additionally company, role and offer key details</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>HubSpot (CRM; EU data centre Frankfurt; the provider is a US company certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework — certain service data may be processed in the USA). Acceptance receipts additionally by email to both parties and in an access-restricted directory of our hosting (EU)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>Contact data as a rule 3 years after the last interaction; newsletter until you unsubscribe; contract and acceptance records 10 years (Art. 958f CO)</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><Bot size={18} /> <h3>Chat assistant "Effi"</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Answering questions about our services directly on the website</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>Your chat messages and the conversation history of the current session; contact details only if you provide them explicitly and consent to forwarding (then to HubSpot, see above)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>DeepSeek (AI provider) — processing takes place on the provider's servers, presumably in China, a country without an adequate level of data protection within the meaning of the revFADP</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>We do not store chat histories; the history ends with the session. The AI provider's own policy applies on its side</dd></div>
    </dl>
    <div class="dp-note">
      <p><strong>Plain language:</strong> What you type into the chat is transmitted to DeepSeek to generate the answer. Do not enter personal data, client data or confidential information there — for anything confidential, use the <a href="/en/contact/">contact form</a> or call us. Using the chat is voluntary; it only runs once you actively open it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><Briefcase size={18} /> <h3>Job applications (career portal)</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Processing your application and — if it fits — inclusion in the specialist pool</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>Name, address, email, phone, salary expectation, workload, referral, and your documents (CV, certificates, cover letter)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>Stored in an access-restricted directory of our hosting (EU); delivered by email to the owner; contact and key details (without files) additionally in the CRM (HubSpot, see above)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>For the duration of the process; if added to the specialist pool, for as long as collaboration remains a possibility. Deletion any time on simple request</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="dp-card">
    <div class="dp-head"><ShieldCheck size={18} /> <h3>Spam protection (Cloudflare Turnstile)</h3></div>
    <dl>
      <div><dt>Purpose</dt><dd>Protecting our forms from automated abuse — without image puzzles</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Data</dt><dd>Technical connection and device data for bot detection; only loads once you use a form</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Recipient &amp; location</dt><dd>Cloudflare (USA; certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Retention</dt><dd>Per Cloudflare's policy; we only receive the check result</dd></div>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2><Scale size={20} class="h-icon" /> 3. Legal Bases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent</strong> — newsletter (double opt-in), forwarding your contact details from the chat, job applications</li>
    <li><strong>Contract or pre-contractual steps</strong> — contact requests, quotes, project delivery</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — operating and securing the website, web statistics, abuse prevention</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — retention where the law requires it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2><Globe size={20} class="h-icon" /> 4. Disclosure Abroad</h2>
  <p>Data may reach the following countries: the <strong>EU</strong> (hosting, HubSpot data centre), the <strong>USA</strong> (Google, Cloudflare, HubSpot service data — each certified under the Swiss–U.S. Data Privacy Framework, which Switzerland has recognized as adequate since 15 September 2024; standard contractual clauses in addition) and — exclusively for the voluntary chat assistant — <strong>China</strong> (DeepSeek, no adequate level of protection; use is based on your voluntary input, see the plain-language note above).</p>

  <h2><Clock size={20} class="h-icon" /> 5. Retention</h2>
  <p>The periods are stated per service in section 2. The principle: we keep data only as long as the purpose requires or the law demands — after that, it is deleted.</p>

  <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
  <div class="info-box">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong> (Art. 25 FADP) — what data we process about you</li>
      <li><strong>Rectification</strong> of inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Deletion</strong> of your data</li>
      <li><strong>Data release and portability</strong> (Art. 28 FADP)</li>
      <li><strong>Objection</strong> to processing and <strong>withdrawal</strong> of consent, at any time</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <p>An email to <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com">me@eflury.com</a> is enough — you will receive a personal reply. You may also complain to the <strong>Swiss Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner (FDPIC)</strong>; where the GDPR applies, also to your local supervisory authority.</p>

  <h2>7. Cookies &amp; Local Storage</h2>
  <p>Details on cookies are in the <a href="/en/cookies/">cookie policy</a>. In addition, your browser locally remembers (localStorage) your design preference (light/dark) — this information never leaves your device.</p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>Transmission is encrypted throughout (TLS), storage is access-restricted, and we minimize: forms only ask for what the purpose requires, and in our own AI demonstrations we pseudonymize data before API calls — the same standard we recommend to clients.</p>

  <h2>9. Changes</h2>
  <p>We update this policy when services or the legal situation change; the version published here is authoritative. The date of the last update is shown above.</p>
</ContentPageLayout>

<style>
  .dp-controller {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    padding: 0.35rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .dpc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dpc-row {
    padding: 0.9rem 0;
  }

  .dpc-row dt {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--teal-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .dpc-row dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .dpc-row dd a {
    color: var(--teal-text);
  }

  .dp-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .dp-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .dp-head :global(svg) {
    color: var(--teal-text);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .dp-head h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dp-card dl {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem 0.9rem;
  }

  .dp-card dl > div {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--separator, var(--border-color));
  }

  .dp-card dl > div:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .dp-card dt {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--teal-text);
    padding-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .dp-card dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .dp-note {
    margin: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--action-teal);
    border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
  }

  .dp-note p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .dp-note a {
    color: var(--teal-text);
  }

  :global(.h-icon) {
    color: var(--teal-text);
    vertical-align: -3px;
    margin-right: 0.35rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .dpc-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .dp-card dl > div {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.15rem;
    }
  }
</style>
